          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>For any function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex>, the type of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000W.xml" title="inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000W" type="local">inverses</fr:link> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>18</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-0044/0</fr:addr><fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0044/0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="being invertible is a proposition › forest://erct/erct-0044/0"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0044.xml" title="being invertible is a proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-0044" type="local">being <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000W.xml" title="inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000W" type="local">invertible</fr:link> is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link></fr:link> › forest://erct/erct-0044/0</fr:title><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>Without loss of generality, we may assume that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> has an <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000W.xml" title="inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000W" type="local">inverse</fr:link> 
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen g,\epsilon ,\eta ,\chi \right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
. By <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0026.xml" title="propositions are closed under retracts" addr="forest://erct/erct-0026" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-0026" /></fr:link>, it suffices to argue that the type of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">inverses</fr:link> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0025.xml" title="retract" addr="forest://erct/erct-0025" type="local">retract</fr:link> of a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>; the type of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">inverses</fr:link> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is in fact equivalent to the type of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">sections</fr:link> equipped with a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0041.xml" title="the coherent remainder of a section" addr="forest://erct/erct-0041" type="local">coherent remainder</fr:link>:</html:p>
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \mathchoice {\textstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \sigma :\mathsf {section}\,f\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \sigma :\mathsf {section}\,f\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \sigma :\mathsf {section}\,f\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \sigma :\mathsf {section}\,f\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}
  \mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{f}\sigma 
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <html:p>By <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001M.xml" title="dependent sum of propositions" addr="forest://erct/erct-001M" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-001M" /></fr:link>, it suffices to show that the type of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">sections</fr:link> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link> and that for every such <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">section</fr:link>, the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0041.xml" title="the coherent remainder of a section" addr="forest://erct/erct-0041" type="local">coherent remainder</fr:link> thereof is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>. The latter is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0043.xml" title="the coherent remainder of a section is a proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-0043" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-0043" /></fr:link>, and the former follows from <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002Q.xml" title="sections of sections are unique" addr="forest://erct/erct-002Q" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-002Q" /></fr:link> by means of the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">retraction</fr:link> 
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen g,\eta \right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
